Reasoning: The paper discusses hardness measures and lower bounds for resolution, which are topics related to computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses measures of width, space, and size of resolution proofs, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses logical aspects of resolution, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the hardness of instances in SAT solving, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
